 null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2017-02-18T08:00:53Z", "updated_at": "2021-03-09T06:55:20Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "With #1304 `update` now has `--reobtain-data`, which maintains content availability on a per-file basis when upgrading. A possible extension could be to have some sort of `--reobtain-data-strategy` option that is set to 'file' by default (current behavior), but different strategies are available. Here is a list of potentially interesting ones:\r\n\r\n- 'files': current behavior\r\n- 'directories-complete': obtain content of all files in all directories that had all files with content prior update (originally suggested in #101)\r\n- 'directories-new': gets anything new in any directory that had any file with content prior update\r\n- 'new': get content for anything new in the entire dataset\r\n\r\nAll three new ones should be relatively straightforward to implement in the present `update`, by amending the filtering of the list of files with content that is already produced.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1313/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1313/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}